Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Associate Software Developer (DevSupport)* with *ISN*. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack web applications, database management, and technical troubleshooting, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade backend systems that directly reflect *the analytical rigor and SQL proficiency this position demands*. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I developed an MCP interaction layer translating natural-language into validated tool calls across 1,000+ endpoints — a project that required deep logic analysis and proactive root cause identification for complex system behaviors. To ensure operational stability, I architected a robust observability layer using Langfuse and LangSmith for tracing and structured logs, enabling me to troubleshoot agentic workflows and monitor real-time application performance. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I directly supported internal users and infrastructure. I built a support chatbot using LangChain, RAG, and PostgreSQL, which reduced ticket resolution time by 20% by enabling natural language queries for root cause identification over documentation. I also designed a cloud storage service using Python and PostgreSQL to handle complex SQL queries for data validation and analysis across S3, GCS, and MinIO. My work on an IAM platform using React, Spring Boot, and AWS RDS involved managing large datasets and implementing stored procedures and logic for 30+ applications, both of which required *the kind of systems-level thinking and operational stability focus this role demands*. Together, these roles have prepared me to *contribute meaningfully to the ISNetworld application's stability and the team's support workflows* and drive impact within an agile engineering team.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in model development, data analysis, and technical communication — skills that translate directly into *the culture of service, integrity, and proactive troubleshooting this team values*. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion, leveraging HPC clusters to analyze and validate large-scale model training. Beyond my technical research, I led technical workshops for 50+ students on building AI Agents and GPU programming. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex system behaviors and technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring *the collaborative communication and cross-functional support responsibilities central to this role*. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to *ISN and its mission of sustainable business solutions*.


I have always been passionate about *Integrity and Service* and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of *helping customers protect people and responsibly source goods and services*. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

